In fact, that may be another Pantheon pattern:

Freedom without structure is noise. Structure without freedom is stagnation.

The interesting region is where exploration is wide enough to discover something new, but disciplined enough that what survives can be carried into the next conversation, the next project, or the next generation. That’s where a melody becomes more than a tune—it becomes a tradition, a movement, or a body of knowledge that other minds can reliably reconstruct.